<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=266&amp;p=1751#p1751"><![CDATA[
The ptimer is always clocked, when there is a condition to silence the channel the output as you say is 0, but ptimer doesnt stop counting (decrementing) and the period is set to the 11  bit value plus *one*.<br /><br />I implement it in that way in my emulator and i think its correct. <img src="http://forums.nesdev.com/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" /><p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=72">Anes</a> — Sun Apr 03, 2005 6:38 pm</p><hr />
